 and critic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Canadian.2bisacsh1 aAleichem, Sholom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBabel, Isaak, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBension, Ariel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernheim, Alfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuber, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaplan, Usher, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChagall, Bella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDworkin, Evlin Yehoash, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEhrenburg, Ilya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEllmann, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlatzer, Nahum N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGold, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldstick, Isidore, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrafstein, Melech, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHecht, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirshprung, Pinchos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJeffers, Robinson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKafka, Franz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennedy, Leo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKesten, Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rel